David,

I found out what the problem was, and it wasn't CVS or SF at all. The client 
I am working for has locked out the CVS protocol from certain sites. So 
while I could browse the JUnit 4 repository with ViewCVS, it was blocking my 
attempts to check code out regardless of which tool I used. Unfortunately I 
wasn't interpreting the error in a way that would lead me to that 
conclusion. Once I tried from a computer that was not on this client's LAN 
CVS worked fine.

Thanks for the reply. It helped me diagnose the problem. Sorry again for the 
noise; I just knew SF couldn't be down that long... <G>
